From bc4559989b382d0fd959dd46bb14f3d0a01fe20d Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Nadia Chambers <nadia.yvette.chambers@ik.me>
Date: Thu, 11 Jun 2026 12:33:13 +0200
Subject: [PATCH 140/174] mm: fix PFN_PTE_SHIFT for page clustering across
 arches

Several arches define PFN_PTE_SHIFT as PAGE_SHIFT (or PAGE_SHIFT-relative), assuming the PTE PFN field sits at the kernel page shift.  Under page clustering the hardware PTE field stays at MMUPAGE granularity while PAGE_SHIFT grows, so the unmasked stride in pte_advance_pfn() (used by set_ptes()/folio_pte_batch()) runs PAGE_MMUCOUNT times too far -- benign on small memory (it just disables batching) but a reserved-bit fault once it overflows the physical-address width on large memory.  Convert the affected arches to MMUPAGE_SHIFT (sparc32: MMUPAGE_SHIFT - 4, matching its SRMMU PPN position).  Arches with a fixed-position PFN_PTE_SHIFT (alpha, riscv, parisc, m68k/sun3), already-MMUPAGE-relative ones (s390, mips, loongarch), and arm64 (own MMUPAGE pte_advance_pfn) are unaffected.  powerpc is left for a separate change since its PFN_PTE_SHIFT aliases PTE_RPN_SHIFT.  Identity when PAGE_MMUSHIFT == 0.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 <noreply@anthropic.com>
---
 arch/arc/include/asm/pgtable-levels.h    | 2 +-
 arch/arm/include/asm/pgtable.h           | 2 +-
 arch/csky/include/asm/pgtable.h          | 2 +-
 arch/m68k/include/asm/mcf_pgtable.h      | 2 +-
 arch/m68k/include/asm/motorola_pgtable.h | 2 +-
 arch/microblaze/include/asm/pgtable.h    | 2 +-
